Food here is AMAZING. Drinks as well! However, the new girl that started 2 days ago made me take 1 star away. I just don’t think it was right for her to get obviously upset and change her demeanor when she forgot to add the sauce and we proceeded to ask for it (since it was part of our order). Simple customer service. If you’re at fault, apologize and make sure the customer is happy. After all, we paid for it and did not give her a hard time like other people would’ve! Nonetheless, I will never stop eating here!

I have finally found tacos in Gainesville that are well worth becoming a weekly routine. I've tried all of the restaurants and little hot spots that people have recommended, and they've each been pretty mediocre. I ate both the shrimp and steak tacos for lunch today, but I'm 110% sure I'm shamelessly going back there for dinner to try something else off the menu. Amazing place!!! Such a great location and even better food!!! Pet friendly and they even have a doggie meal ! I had the steak tacos and it was so delicious I wanted to eat again there the next day. I can’t wait til next weekend so I can take my mom and my puppy for a treat. Thank you for the amazing food Muñecas!!

We were looking for a hot dog place we heard about and stumbled onto this place, awesome! Place has lots of character.  Used to be a gas station and is registered as a historical building.  Plenty of tables with outside seating only.  Staff/owners were friendly and helpful.  Menu has plenty to choose from.  Tacos, quesadillas, chips, salsa, guacamole, sodas, beer, etc.  We got the mojo pork and chicken tacos along with steak quesadillas and chips with pico de gallo.  Cokes and lager draft beer.  All excellent.  Prices are fair and quality very good.  Would we go back? You bet your refried beans we would!

No. They're slipping. At least through delivery or pickup this has become a horrendous version of what it once was. It used to be a quick decent bite to eat, with a little lacking in flavor but overall worth the price. Maybe it's losing money but at this point it's inconsistent as to whether you'll get any of the additions you ask for and mind you, if you don't pay  an extra $0.50 per vegetable, it's not about getting extra. Be prepared to receive rice, meat and a couple pieces of potato. Pay an extra 2 bucks to maybe add some salt or seasoning and flavor to an otherwise fairly bland base with diluted curry sauce, and you may or may not be lucky enough to receive it. Quick, adequate, reasonably priced, huge portions.  Maybe I'm jaded because I miss Tasty Buddha and its cozy quick curry and fried rice dishes. Steamers had the same idea, but just not quite as good flavor wise. They make up for, or rather mask, the lack of authentic seasoning with heat. So if you enjoy spice, get it as hot as you can handle and you'll probably still enjoy it.  There's a huge amount though so you can reheat and reseason the leftovers the next day.  Personally enjoy the peanut sauce addition, gives a little bit of flavor but the veggies and meat need something. The steamer sandwich is not recommended, but only tried it once.  It's presumably their special, but stick to the fried rice and curry dishes if in the area. If willing to spend a little more money, go to if it is down the street for delicious authentic Thai.

Description: Legend be told, Steamers was apparently this awesome place a little while back where students and residents of Gainesville alike would come and enjoy a good bite to eat. Unfortunately, I was unable to experience any of this; however, it might not be a bad thing after all. I read an article that Ken Eats Gainesville wrote about this place called Steamers reopening in Bo Didley Plaza and I knew it was fate... Actually that's not true. When I first heard the name, I instantly thought about this awful place back in my hometown and thought they were the same restaurant.  Food & Service: Getting a little off topic, anyways, I went with a friend just last week to go and check the place out myself. I was thrown off when their menu consisted of fried rice and curry with woks lined up in plain view. Apparently the name comes from steaming their burgers but the fried rice and curry seem to be more popular. Steamers is also considered vegetarian on Yelp, just a tad confusing in my opinion. Despite the confusion, I appreciated their water dispenser and outside seating. This is definitely the kind of place you could bring your friends to hang out and eat on one of their benches. The food took a little longer than expected but the portions were huge! Unless you're starving, you'll probably need a box. Price was very reasonable, we paid about $8.00 or $9.00 each. My friend ordered the fried rice which was pretty flavorful and cooked well. I ordered the curry with tempeh. I was told their tempeh was pretty awesome and I wouldn't disagree. Note that this was my first time having tempeh though lol.  Final Thoughts: All in all, good place to stop by and eat! I'll be back and probably with a group of friends this time since the outdoor seating gives a nice catch up, get together feeling. I also want to give their steamer burger a try.
One of the best curries I've had in gainesville and the second tastiest chicken fried rice here too. Can't wait to try the rest of the menu!
My favorite place to grab a quick bite. Especially the twisted Indonesian chicken or house? Spice level of 7 and a double side of their fresh habanero sauce? Oh mmmmyyyyyyyy!

I was not at all impressed with this restaurant. I had jury duty at the civil courthouse which is RIGHT THERE and decided to try this place because I thought it would be something quick. Boy was I wrong. By the time I finally got my food I only had 10 minutes to inhale it out of my hour break. The House Special, which has chicken and steak with the fried rice, was only OK. Definitely not worth the price ($9.99+tax) nor the wait time. The portion was huge, I will give them that, but when you can't take it with you and only have 10 minutes to eat once the food is finally done most of it goes in the trash. It was a wasted $11.
